	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=485&mid=102561300646286>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=485&mid=102561300646286>Staff Update</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=485&mid=102561300646286#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Jul 2nd 8:40 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=68492><span id= >necrro</span></a><br><span id=notbold>61 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.35]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This dropped for me on Tholuxe Paells last nite (7/01/02).&nbsp;&nbsp;Just some clarification.  I am 53 Necro and could single pull anything down there with no trouble.  Xalgoz is undead.  Shackle of SPirit and your pet with Aug on him rock the house.  I would pull with Shackle and sick pet and med.  Pet tore everything up easily (49th tanker version pet..not the Rogue pet).  I also loaded up engulfing for the spectral stuff because it ran on low health, all the skellies mobs did not run.  Exp was decent even though most stuff was green.  Even with two mobs on the pet, if they are slowed he wins everytime.  <br><br>Best way I found to fight him with pet is to park just off to the right of the front of the Church against the wall.  Clear the spawns in front and pull him with Annul to get rid of his buffs (he always has up Banshee Aura).  Spam /pet back off until Xalgoz gets to you.  He will cast on you but almost nothing sticks and its all low level stuff anyway.  Then EB him, BoD, engulf and let pet kill him.  Don't fight inside church unless you do not care about adds from the basement.<br><br>As for his casting:  he starts by casting chilling embrace on you a couple times.  If you have up DMF it never sticks.  He also casts Boil Blood, Dooming, Scourge and Invoke Fear.  I usually buffed pet with Resist Disease and DMF because of these spells.<br><br>The only spell that ever stuck to me was Boil Blood and that was irrelevant because BOD is more than sufficient to counteract that affect.  I have lousy gear, crappy resists and not good intel and this camp was a breeze.<br><br>About faction.  I started off with Outpost at Kindly.  I was down there about 3 days killing stuff.  I ended up with Kindly.  The hits are miniscule.<br><br><br>One last note.  There is a post on this board about how to get to the Church.  I think in the Xalgoz section.  Its an excellent road map.  I followed it to the &quot;T&quot; and walked down to the church myself using Invis and Invis undead and FD.  It was very easy and involved no dangerous trains.  <br><br>P.S. - Post is by Ishtarra, Scholar in the Xalgoz message board thread.  Follow those isntructions and you can get there easily by yourself.<br><br>Xalgoz - spawn time:  30 minutes.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Jul  2 08:37:43 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Necrro Mancer<br>61th Warlock of Tholuxe Paells (Misty Knight)</td></td></tr>
